election_record.label: Vermont 1818 Council

overview.note: The Original Election Returns tally sheet lists the Federalist candidate Heman Allen as "Heman Allen of Milton." It lists a second Heman Allen as "Heman Allen Colchester." The two men were cousins. Heman Allen of Colchester had been elected to Congress from Vermont in 1816.
Timothy Stanley, Thomas Hammond and John Willard were Republicans who were also on the Federalist list.

sub_unit.name: Addison
sub_unit.note: The Original Election Returns tally sheet lists 1344 votes for Timothy Stanley, 1856 votes for Thomas Hammond, 1003 votes for Aaron Leland, 1110 votes for William Cahoon, 902 votes for Frederick Bliss, 1009 votes for Ezra Butler, 294 votes for John Willard, 346 votes for Herman Allen, 417 votes for Elias Lyman and 345 votes for Isaac Fletcher. The town votes in the original returns, however, add up to the totals listed here.

sub_unit.name: Bennington
sub_unit.note: The Original Election Returns tally sheet lists 796 votes for Pliny Smith in Bennington County; however, the sum of totals per town is 794.

sub_unit.name: Caledonia
sub_unit.note: The Original Election Returns tally sheet lists 1133 votes for Thomas Chittenden and 1147 votes for Daniel Peaslee in Caledonia County.

sub_unit.name: Chittenden
sub_unit.note: The original returns do not list in which town the votes for Isaac Barley, William D. Forest, William Hanes, Calvin Jewett, and Aaron Robinson were cast.
The Original Election Returns tally sheet lists 818 votes for William Cahoon in Chittenden County.

sub_unit.name: Essex
sub_unit.note: The Original Election Returns tally sheet lists 225 votes for Thomas Hammond, 221 votes for Aaron Leland, 221 votes for William Cahoon, 223 votes for Theophilus Crawford, 223 votes for Truman Chittenden, 222 votes for Frederick Bliss and 221 votes for Ezra Butler.

sub_unit.name: Franklin
sub_unit.note: The Original Election Returns tally sheet lists 786 votes for Thomas Hammond, 748 votes for Aaron Leland, 762 votes for William Cahoon, 759 votes for Frederick Bliss, 756 votes for Ezra Butler and 217 votes for Elias Lyman in Franklin County.

sub_unit.name: Franklin
sub_unit.note: In 1818, the town of Huntsburgh was renamed Franklin.

sub_unit.name: Grand Isle
sub_unit.note: The Original Election Returns tally sheet lists 170 votes for Thomas Hammond, 158 votes for Ezra Butler and 54 votes for Horatio Seymour in Grand Isle County.

sub_unit.name: Alburgh
sub_unit.note: Horatio Seymour received 8 votes as Horasho Seman.

sub_unit.name: Grand Isle
sub_unit.note: Horatio Seymour received 34 votes as Horasho Seman.

sub_unit.name: Orange
sub_unit.note: The Original Election Returns tally sheet lists 1560 votes for Truman Chittenden, 1522 votes for Pliny Smith, 1472 votes for Frederick Bliss, 1566 votes for Ezra Butler, 316 votes for John Willard, 125 votes for Zerah Willoby and 154 votes for Isaac Fletcher.

sub_unit.name: Orleans
sub_unit.note: The Original Election Returns tally sheet lists 440 votes for Truman Chittenden and 482 votes for Frederick Bliss.

sub_unit.name: Washington
sub_unit.note: The Original Election Returns tally sheet for Washington County uses the spelling How for William Howe.

sub_unit.name: Windsor
sub_unit.note: The Original Election Returns tally sheet lists 2609 votes for Timothy Stanley, 2766 for Thomas Hammond, 2559 for William Cahoon, 2463 for Theophilus Crawford, 2434 for Truman Chittenden, 2476 for Pliney Smith, 2427 for Frederick Bliss, 2438 for Ezra Butler, 1181 for Daniel Peaslee, 1556 for Abel Tomlinson, 1282 for John Willard, 1400 for Beriah Loomis, 195 for Herman Allen, and 358 for Elias Lyman.
